                "question": "According to the schematic in panel (a), how is \u201cSelective N\u2082O application\u201d physically achieved during the ALD cycle?",
                "answer_type": "Paragraph",
                "answer": "Pulse substitution. The N\u2082O plasma step is selectively substituted only during a specific cation sub-cycle (e.g., Gallium or Indium), while O\u2082 plasma is used for the remaining cation layers."
